This paper deals with the Chord distributed hash table, which is a well-known and frequently used data structure in peer-to-peer systems. The paper provides a specification of correct operations and initialization for Chord, an inductive invariant that is necessary and sufficient to support a proof of correctness, and the proof itself. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modeling and analysis of the Chord protocol, which could also place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories.
